# "Bucureștiul Posibil" - Quick Reference

## Project Overview
Interactive citizen-engagement map at **bucurestiulposibil.ro** where citizens propose urban improvements for Bucharest. Moderated workflow: User proposals → Sanity CMS → Approval → D1 sync → Map display.

**Stack**: Next.js 15 + React 19 + TypeScript + Leaflet + Sanity + Cloudflare D1/Workers

## Key UI Elements
- **Full-screen map** bounded to Bucharest with custom pins
- **Top-left**: Clickable logo → project info modal  
- **Top-right**: + button (active after pin placement) → proposal form
- **Bottom-right**: Search/Help/GPS controls + zoom
- **Pin workflow**: Click map → place orange pin → fill form → submit → moderation → approval → live pin

## Data Flow
```
User proposal → /api/propose-point → Sanity (pending) → 
Human approval → Webhook → /api/sanity-webhook → D1 sync → Map display
```

## Critical Files
- `MapPage.tsx` (823 lines): Main UI, modals, controls
- `Map.tsx` (272 lines): Leaflet integration, pin popups  
- `propose-point/route.ts`: Proposal API endpoint
- `sanity-webhook/route.ts`: Sync handler (Sanity → D1)
- `geopoints/route.ts`: Map data API (D1 → Frontend)
- `locationStore.ts`: Frontend cache and D1 interface
- `geopoint.ts`: TypeScript interfaces for all data

## Dev Workflow Essentials
```bash
npm run test:run      # Must pass (34/34 tests)
npm run lint          # Must be clean
npm run check         # Full validation pipeline
npm run cf-typegen    # After Cloudflare changes
```

## Key Rules
- ✅ Only approved pins exist in D1 (webhook enforces)
- ✅ All proposals start as pending in Sanity
- ✅ Tests must pass before committing
- ❌ Never use `any` types (ESLint enforced)

## Database Schema
- **Sanity**: Full pin documents with status workflow
- **D1**: `geopoints` table with lat/lng indices and submitter fields
- **Frontend**: Cached Location objects with submittedByName for popups

## Popup Display
Existing pins show: Title, Description, and **submitter name in bold at bottom** (no prefix label)

